annotation.TEXT: Now, Yamame's gotta be descending by this point. (Don't question how she doesn't burn up on reentry!)
It's still gonna take a while. Better speed it up some more.
Once you start going over the branch, just keep holding in the same direction to build up speed.
There I am. It shows me at 192nd, but I actually share 184th with nine others at this time.

When you land, you'll see how far she went. Then, you can press Z to try again, or press Space to return to the title screen. I guess Shift is used to Tweet your score or something, but I never use that.
Okay, let's get a halfway-decent toss here!
Unlike most of these flash games, even the quality option is in Japanese, but it should be easy enough to figure out. Also, the bottom option returns you to the main menu.
And I'm just 18cm behind second place, and about 17m away from first! Wow...
I'm still kind of in shock that I just pulled that off. Oftentimes, I'll get around 70,000-90,000 when I get a good-looking launch, with 100K occurring rarely. But this is just amazing!

Another thing you can do is change her pose with the up and down arrow keys. There are four different poses, but I don't think they have any effect on your distance (though I'm not 100% sure about that).
Oops, went over the top again... At least retrying takes very little time. (I hate games or mini-games where the restarting process takes forever!)
And, it looks like I'm the top dog when it comes to landing Yamame upright (which really isn't that hard to do)!
Of course, what goes up, must come down!
Ooh, this could be good. You want the string to come as close to the top as possible without going over (just like The Price is Right). Then, try to launch at a 45 degree angle at the lower-right.
Yes, you can go over the top of the branch in this mode! This can get you some insane velocity, and this is what that other leaderboards (with scores all over 100,000m) is for!
HOLY CRACKERS!!! I can't believe I just walloped my old score, and I did it while recording this video!
Hmm... I think my angle was too high. I'm thinking that the best angle will just barely make UFOs visible and won't even come close to seeing satellites.
Umm... That didn't go well.
Also, the heart I believe indicates that Yamame landed upright with that score, which I do every time I have a halfway-decent launch.
I'm over 9000!
I wonder what the highest amount you could technically score is, if all elements were exactly perfect... (I also wonder that about the normal mode as well...)
Whoops! What kind of silly launch was that? Well, I'll just drive her head first into the ground.
Yep, having this happen multiple times is fairly common for me, but retrying takes very little time, so it's no big deal.
Then, when you're feeling lucky, press Z, and hopefully, you'll go up and right, and not straight into the ground!
Oh, by the way, my best score for this leaderboard put me in 25th. Not bad at all!
There's a point after about 20-30 seconds of holding the button where the effectiveness of this maxes out though, so there's no need to hold it for minutes/hours/days!
Okay, there we go. I think this is as long as the string can possibly get, where the tip of Yamame's head is barely grazing the ground.

I'm not exactly sure what all this means though. Maybe the upper numbers indicate the total cumulative distances achieved by everybody that has played the game or something, but I'm not sure, and I can't even venture a guess on the lower numbers.

And finally, we have this fifth option, which I think is unlocked when you achieve a certain distance while playing. (UPDATE: Actually, SuperSupermario24 informed me that it's from playing the normal game 3 times, regardless of distance achieved.)

You kind of really have to get lucky in order to get a launch that goes up and right at max speed, and if you are super lucky, you might just break 100,000m! (So, yeah. I consider my 25th place score to be very lucky!)
My old best:
The fourth option displays... this.
Yeah, what you're supposed to do is press Z before Yamame hits the ground. Then, use the left and right arrow keys to start swinging her back and forth.
Oof! You'll probably see that happen a lot.
Okay, I got the maximum length string again.
Okay, well, let's go back to the title screen and see what my new rank is!

Okay, now if you do ever somehow manage to score high enough to get on the leaderboards, type your name into the box (mine is already there since I've done this previously), then click the left button to register it. (I'm assuming the right button declines the registration.)
I want to at least break 220m in this recording, so I'm going to keep trying for a while here.
Okay, now the third option on the title screen lets you adjust the game's volume levels, along with the graphics quality.
Ludicrous speed! (Octuple speed!)
GAAHHH!!! Nuts!
Still too slow. I'm expecting a score in the 70K-90K range. Maybe 100K if I'm really lucky. So, let's speed it up even more!
It's apparent what the approximate upper limit you can achieve is, as all of the scores are in the 227m area, including my best score (which is in a multi-way tie for 184th place).
From here, press Z to return to the main menu.
Just what could this leaderboard possibly pertain to? Well, I'll get to that in a moment.
Now, the second option is the leaderboards. It shows the top 300 scores, and you can view the different pages by pressing up or down.
Oops! Don't swing all the way over the top of the tree branch though, or else this'll happen!

Too bad there's not much in the way of scenery up here, aside from an occasional flickering satellite. (Come on, not even a starry background? I am practically in outer space at this point. (Umm... Don't question how Yamame can still breathe and stay alive.))
Third place! I'm now in third place! That's just awesome!
Oh, and you can change your pose at almost any time, not just when she's flying through the air.
Double speed!
If you happened to launch backwards, or practically straight up, or some other angle that didn't look good to you, you can save yourself some time by refreshing the page.
Now, if you press left or right, you can view a different leaderboard, where all of the scores are above 100,000m!

It should only take a few seconds to get back into the game after a refresh, compared to several minutes of waiting for Yamame to land. (Too bad you can't use Space to instantly restart like in Myon Toss...)

Here, on the title screen, we've got a bunch of options to choose from. Use the up and down arrow keys to move the cursor, and press Z to choose an option. For now, I'll just choose the top one to start the game. I'll go over the others later.
Ooh, there we go! I got a launch that went up and right! That's what I wanted to show for this recording!
Note: It is possible to get Yamame to land on her feet after going over the top like that, but it's tricky to do.
Who knows how high this will go, but one thing's for sure-- It'll be at least a few minutes before Yamame lands, so I think I'll start speeding up the recording.
Hello, and welcome to another Touhou flash game! This time, it's Yamame Swing!
Okay, I'm over 90,000, so I'm gonna be landing soon for sure, so I've returned the speed to normal.
Over 95,000... This is definitely a very good launch.
Now, this looks like the same game, but there's a major difference...
Now, when you do get a good launch like this, it'll probably take a few minutes before Yamame lands.
Seriously, though. I did not expect such an amazing score to occur while recording! I was just looking for something reasonably decent, not a record-breaker!
Okay, 210.10m is not bad, but my high score is above 227m, so let's see if I can do better than this.
She can actually land upright (and then gives you a wink)!
Darn, I think I launched at too high an angle again.
Yeah, that's a negative toss. You can launch backwards, though there's no point. I'll often intentionally launch Yamame into the ground if the string is not at maximum length, though.
Still, how well did I do? We'll find out within the next half-minute or so!
If she goes high enough, you'll start seeing UFOs, satellites, and a starry background. They're just for decoration and don't affect gameplay.
Also, once you're airborne, you can use left and right to adjust your rotation. If you make Yamame point straight vertically with her feet towards the ground...
Yeah, that's way too high.
Alright, I think that's enough for now. I'm not going to waste all day on this. So, let's go back to the title screen and explore the other options.
Now, I'm over 10,000, and I'm just going to keep on going for a while!
Quadruple speed!
Oh, by the way, you see how Yamame's flickering all over the place when her speed gets insane? Well, it's even more flicker-tastic than what YouTube's 30 FPS is showing here!
Oh, man! I actually pulled off 100,000 here! This could get interesting, folks! I'll show my current record above the distance counter.
Oww... That's okay. I'm sure Yamame is just as eager as me to try again!
Argh... I hate it when it looked like it just barely went over the top like that.
My best:
Okay, now once you're swinging, press Z one more time to launch Yamame! Try to launch her as far to the right as possible!
Well, I think I've shown off everything I wanted to show off here, and then some! See you all later!
